CatDescriptText: Related article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1956, pg. A24, reads: "Bus Trip Set For Cleveland - If you'd like to tour the scenic spots of Cleveland, Ohio, and see the New York Yankees play the Cleveland Indians, you can do so and have a lot of fun too, on Aug. 2. That's the date when members of the Youth Department of Centre Ave. YMCA will travel by special bus to Ohio for 'Operations Cleveland.'  The tourists will visit the Cedar Ave. Branch of YMCA, where they will swim and meet other youngsters.  The return trip will be made by way of the Pennsylvania Turnpike.  Parents are welcome to come along on the trip, which will serve as a vacation for many youths.  Additional information may be obtained by calling the YMCA MA 1-1762."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of boys, women, and men, posed in front of Greyhound bus with sign reading "Centre Ave. YMCA 'Operations' Cleveland, Ohio, Aug. 2nd, 1956" and "first annual benefit car wash...", posed in front of Centre Avenue YMCA, Hill District
